EmailTemplate.name: HT 2017 - Final Email
EmailTemplate.subject: Haiti Public Build - Two weeks to go!
EmailTemplate.textOnly:
Hey everyone,
Can you believe that in a couple of weeks you will be in Haiti?! I am so excited for each of you to experience this trip.
Before you take off, we have some important information and reminders. There is a lot of important information below. Please take the time to read it thoroughly!
Please note that if you have any questions, please email me before May 2nd so that I can get back to you promptly. I am taking vacation time from May 3-21st and it will be hard to answer my emails. However, I will be checking my emails when I can during the trip. For emergency inquiries, you are able to call the office at 905-777-1662 and anyone can assist you. Our staff in the office will also be checking our builds@livedifferent.com email as well, so please feel free use that email. If it's not urgent, you can wait for me to send you an email back. But please, try to connect with me over the next few days!
1. ARRIVAL and ACCOMMODATIONS
When you arrive into Cap Haitien, our staff will be waiting for you as you come out of the airport. They will be wearing a Live Different t-shirt or holding a Live Different Build sign. They will bring you to the hotel to settle in.
In Cap-Haitien we will be staying at the Habitation Jouissant. Here is the website: http://www.habitationjouissant.com/
This safe and clean hotel will feel more like a friendly home than a hotel. It has a wonderful view of the bay and they serve amazing food.
This hotel does not offer locked safes in your rooms. Please use caution when considering packing anything of value to you (jewelry, computers, cell phones, etc). You may want to bring a little lock for your luggage.
2. PASSPORTS
Please bring 2 photocopies of your passport with you. One will be given to staff, and the other is for you to keep on yourself. This is a precaution just in case your passport goes missing while travelling.
3. PACKING LIST
Please read through the packing list thoroughly to ensure that you have everything you need for your trip. Often, our volunteers pack the night before and realize that they need to purchase some items. It is easier to do this a week early!
4. EMERGENCY CONTACTS
If your family needs to contact you in case of emergency, these are the numbers to call:
Live Different Build Office:1-866-432-4464 (toll free) Live Different Staff Haiti Number: 011 509-3860-7496 Habitation Jouissant (Cap-Haitien): 011 509-3124-2400
For general inquiries and non-urgent matters, please contact us via email at builds@livedifferent.com.
5. PHONE AND INTERNET ACCESS
There is wi-fi access at the Habitation Jouissant but the internet connection is fairly poor. Please come prepared to be off grid while in Haiti. If you require a phone for emergency use, please feel free to ask our staff to use their phone.
6. SPENDING MONEY/CURRENCY
It is best to bring cash in USD as this is commonly used. Please consider the following when deciding how much spending money to bring:
Your meals while traveling to and from your home to Cap-Haitien, as well as some snacks while in Haiti Any personal spending (for things like souvenirs or snacks) $30 USD Resort staff tip - suggested amount $50 Citadel Excursion $50 Excursion to Amiga Island $25 USD for a night out for dinner in a fun beach hotel with your team.
7. YOUR LIVE DIFFERENT STAFF
Liam, Stacey and Frantzo will be your trip hosts. They're looking forward to meeting you all! (And seeing some familiar faces!)
